sql:
SELECT SUM(num_graduates) AS total_graduates
FROM graduates
WHERE cohort_id = 0;

SELECT AVG(num_students) AS average_students
FROM cohorts
WHERE cohort_year = 2020;

SELECT average_gpa AS average_cohort_gpa
FROM cohorts
WHERE cohort_id = 1;

SELECT SUM(num_non_graduates) AS total_non_graduates
FROM non_graduates
WHERE cohort_id = 1;

SELECT SUM(num_dropouts) AS total_dropouts
FROM dropouts
WHERE cohort_id = 1;

SELECT college_enrollment_rate
FROM graduates
WHERE cohort_id = 1;

SELECT AVG(average_gpa) AS avg_gpa
FROM cohorts
WHERE cohort_year = 2020;

external_knowledge:
Net increase in students refers to the difference between the number of graduates and the sum of dropouts and transfers; 
The district averages are calculated across all schools within the same district; 
The sorting of schools by net increase in students provides insight into which schools and districts are performing better in terms of student retention and success.
